{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879182968,"sessionID":"ses_2855a65b7ffeBfG64odKO022sS","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa5d5a1001Pg9tz8b9lv0iyE","messageID":"msg_d7aa5cce7001k6fjPTVKhI7WiB","sessionID":"ses_2855a65b7ffeBfG64odKO022sS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7243c17e47f741778b7f0236","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD ŌĆö Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` ŌåÆ `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | ŌĆö |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | ŌĆö |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-*` | *(none ŌĆö scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | ŌĆö | ŌĆö |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` ŌåÆ `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` ŌåÆ `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | ŌĆö | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` ŌåÆ `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` ŌåÆ default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` ŌåÆ **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` ŌåÆ **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` ŌåÆ `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) ŌåÆ pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` ŌåÆ `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) ŌåÆ pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` ŌåÆ `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ OWNERS\n131: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ e2e/\n132:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ README.md\n133:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ __init__.py\n134:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ run_e2e.sh\n135:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ e2e_test.go\n136:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ echo_agent.yaml\n138:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` ŌåÆ `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic ŌĆ£install CRDs and agent-sandboxŌĆØ; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD ŌĆö Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summa