main`, `release-*`\n500:    - Job: checkout ŌåÆ setup-go 1.23 ŌåÆ kind-action v0.30.0 (install_only) ŌåÆ set ARTIFACTS_PATH ŌåÆ `make e2e` ŌåÆ on failure upload logs ŌåÆ `always()` ŌåÆ `make e2e-clean`\n501: \n502: ### Phase 2: õ╗ŻńĀüĶ┤©ķćÅ Workflow\n503: \n504: 5. **ÕłøÕ╗║ `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml`** ŌĆö õ╗ŻńĀüńö¤µłÉµŻĆµ¤ź\n505:    - Ķ¦”ÕÅæ: `pull_request` to `main`, `release-*`\n506:    - ĶĘ»ÕŠäĶ┐ćµ╗ż: `codegen` filter\n507:    - Job: checkout ŌåÆ paths-filter ŌåÆ if changed: setup-go 1.24.4 ŌåÆ `make gen-check`\n508: \n509: 6. **ÕłøÕ╗║ `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml`** ŌĆö ńēłµØāµŻĆµ¤ź\n510:    - Ķ¦”ÕÅæ: `pull_request` to `main`, `release-*`\n511:    - ĶĘ»ÕŠäĶ┐ćµ╗ż: `copyright` filter\n512:    - Job: checkout ŌåÆ paths-filter ŌåÆ if changed: apt install moreutils ŌåÆ `make gen-copyright` ŌåÆ `git diff --exit-code`\n513: \n514: 7. **ÕłøÕ╗║ `.github/workflows/codespell.yml`** ŌĆö µŗ╝ÕåÖµŻĆµ¤ź\n515:    - Ķ¦”ÕÅæ: `pull_request` to `main`, `release-*`\n516:    - Job: checkout ŌåÆ backup/remove false-positive files ŌåÆ pip install codespell ŌåÆ codespell with skips/ignores ŌåÆ `always()` restore files\n517: \n518: ### Phase 3: Python Workflow\n519: \n520: 8. **ÕłøÕ╗║ `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml`** ŌĆö Python SDK µĄŗĶ»Ģ\n521:    - Ķ¦”ÕÅæ: `pull_request`, `merge_group`\n522:    - ĶĘ»ÕŠäĶ┐ćµ╗ż: `sdk` filter\n523:    - Job: checkout ŌåÆ paths-filter ŌåÆ if changed: setup-python 3.12 in sdk-python/ ŌåÆ pip install pytest ŌåÆ pip install -e . ŌåÆ `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n524: \n525: 9. **ÕłøÕ╗║ `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`** ŌĆö Python lint\n526:    - Ķ¦”ÕÅæ: `pull_request` to `main`, `release-*`\n527:    - ĶĘ»ÕŠäĶ┐ćµ╗ż: `python` filter\n528:    - Job: checkout ŌåÆ paths-filter ŌåÆ if changed: setup-python 3.10 ŌåÆ pip install ruff ŌåÆ `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n529: \n530: ### Phase 4: ÕÅæÕĖāõĖÄĶć¬ÕŖ©Õī¢ Workflow\n531: \n532: 10. **ÕłøÕ╗║ `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml`** ŌĆö ÕżÜµ×Čµ×äķĢ£ÕāÅÕÅæÕĖā\n533:     - Ķ¦”ÕÅæ: `push` to `main`, tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*`\n534:     - Job: checkout ŌåÆ setup-go 1.24.4 ŌåÆ setup-buildx ŌåÆ docker login ghcr.io ŌåÆ set TAG ŌåÆ `make docker-buildx-push-workloadmanager` ŌåÆ `docker-buildx-push-router` ŌåÆ `docker-buildx-push-picod`\n535: \n536: 11. **ÕłøÕ╗║ `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml`** ŌĆö Dify µÅÆõ╗ČÕÅæÕĖā\n537:     - Ķ¦”ÕÅæ: `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*`\n538:     - Job: download dify-plugin CLI ŌåÆ install yq ŌåÆ read manifest ŌåÆ package plugin ŌåÆ checkout author/dify-plugins with PLUGIN_ACTION ŌåÆ move .difypkg ŌåÆ branch/commit/push ŌåÆ `gh pr create`\n539: \n540: 12. **ÕłøÕ╗║ `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml`** ŌĆö Ķć¬ÕŖ©Õ«Īµē╣\n541:     - Ķ¦”ÕÅæ: `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` to `main`, `release-**`\n542:     - Job: github-script ŌåÆ list contributor PRs ŌåÆ if not first-time or has ok-to-test ŌåÆ list action_required runs ŌåÆ approve each\n543: \n544: ---\n545: \n546: ## 7. ÕÉÄń╗ŁÕÅśµø┤ (Follow-up Changes)\n547: \n548: | ÕÅśµø┤ | µÅÅĶ┐░ | õ╝śÕģłń║¦ |\n549: |------|------|--------|\n550: | Docusaurus µ¢ćµĪŻ CI/CD | µ¢ćµĪŻń½Öńé╣Ķć¬ÕŖ©µ×äÕ╗║ÕÆīķā©ńĮ▓ | õĖŁ |\n551: | Reusable workflows µŖĮĶ▒Ī | Õ░åÕģ¼Õģ▒ńÜä Go/Python Ķ«ŠńĮ«ķĆ╗ĶŠæµÅÉÕÅ¢õĖ║ `workflow_call` ÕÅ»ÕżŹńö© workflow | õĮÄ |\n552: | Self-hosted runners | õĖ║ E2E µĄŗĶ»ĢķģŹńĮ«Ķć¬µēśń«Ī runner õ╗źÕŖĀķĆ¤ Kind ķøåńŠżÕłøÕ╗║ | õĮÄ |\n553: | Slack/Discord ķĆÜń¤ź | CI Õż▒Ķ┤źµŚČÕÅæķĆüķĆÜń¤źÕł░Õøóķś¤ķóæķüō | õĮÄ |\n554: | Ķ”åńø¢ńÄćķśłÕĆ╝ķŚ©ń”ü | Ķ«ŠńĮ«µ£ĆõĮÄĶ”åńø¢ńÄćķśłÕĆ╝’╝īõĮÄõ║ÄķśłÕĆ╝µŚČ PR µŻĆµ¤źÕż▒Ķ┤ź | õĖŁ |\n555: | Dependabot ķģŹńĮ« | Ķć¬ÕŖ©µø┤µ¢░ GitHub Actions õŠØĶĄ¢ńēłµ£¼ | õĖŁ |\n\n(End of file - total 555 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) ŌĆö Design/Ķ«ŠĶ«ĪĶ»┤µśÄ\n\n## 1. µ×Čµ×ä (Architecture)\n\n### 1.1 Õ«ÜõĮŹ (Purpose/Positioning)\n\nõĖ║ AgentCube ķĪ╣ńø«Õ╗║ń½ŗÕ«īµĢ┤ńÜä GitHub Actions CI/CD µĄüµ░┤ń║┐õĮōń│╗’╝īĶ”åńø¢õ╗źõĖŗĶüīĶ┤Ż’╝Ü\n\n1. **PR ķŚ©ń”üķ¬īĶ»ü** ŌĆö Docker µ×äÕ╗║ŃĆüGo lintŃĆürace-enabled Ķ”åńø¢ńÄćµĄŗĶ»ĢŃĆüKind E2E µĄŗĶ»ĢŃĆüõ╗ŻńĀüńö¤µłÉµ╝éń¦╗µŻĆµĄŗŃĆüńēłµØā/µŗ╝ÕåÖµŻĆµ¤źŃĆüPython SDK µĄŗĶ»ĢõĖÄ lint\n2. **Ķć¬ÕŖ©ÕÅæÕĖā** ŌĆö µÄ©ķĆü `main` µł¢Ķ»Łõ╣ēÕī¢ńēłµ£¼ tag µŚČµ×äÕ╗║Õ╣ČµÄ©ķĆüÕżÜµ×Čµ×äÕ«╣ÕÖ©ķĢ£ÕāÅÕł░ GHCR\n3. **µÅÆõ╗ČÕÅæÕĖā** ŌĆö `dify-plugin/v*` tag µŚČµēōÕīģ Dify µÅÆõ╗ČÕ╣ČĶć¬ÕŖ©µÅÉõ║ż PR Õł░ `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n4. **Ķ┤Īńī«ĶĆģõĮōķ¬ī** ŌĆö Ķć¬ÕŖ©Õ«Īµē╣ķØ×ķ”¢µ¼ĪĶ┤Īńī«ĶĆģµł¢ÕĖ” `ok-to-test` µĀćńŁŠńÜä pending workflow runs\n\nµ£¼ AR õĖŹõ┐«µö╣õ╗╗õĮĢńÄ░µ£ēµ║ÉńĀüŃĆüDockerfileŃĆüHelm chart µł¢ Makefile’╝īõ╗ģµČłĶ┤╣ AR-033 Õ«Üõ╣ēńÜä Makefile ńø«µĀćŃĆé\n\n### 1.2 ń│╗ń╗¤õĖŖõĖŗµ¢ć (System Context)\n\n```\nŌöīŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöÉ\nŌöé                        GitHub Repository                                Ōöé","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/design.md","time":{"start":1775879187893,"end":1775879187900}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879189265,"sessionID":"ses_2855a65b7ffeBfG64odKO022sS","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa5ee360017YFjfC2JIBj9mc","messageID":"msg_d7aa5e0d9001EgPYkHHxUEoJeL","sessionID":"ses_2855a65b7ffeBfG64odKO022sS","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3c761e99d3c94fbaa0978d5f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) ŌĆö Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `.github`\n6: - **Language:** YAML\n7: - **Size:** L\n8: - **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the creation of 12 GitHub Actions workflow files under `.github/workflows/` that provide a complete CI/CD pipeline for the AgentCube project. The workflows SHALL cover PR build verification, Go linting, test coverage, E2E testing on Kind, code generation drift checks, copyright/spelling checks, Python SDK tests and linting, multi-architecture release image publication, Dify plugin publishing, and automated workflow approval for repeat contributors. All workflows SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for path-based conditional execution where applicable, and SHALL consume Makefile targets defined in AR-033 without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Workflow 1: main.yml ŌĆö Agentcube CI Workflow\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: Docker build on PR to main/release-*\n19: \n20: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/main.yml` that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: PR to main triggers docker build\n23: - **GIVEN** a pull request targeting the `main` branch\n24: - **WHEN** the `Agentcube CI Workflow` job runs\n25: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: PR to release-* triggers docker build\n28: - **GIVEN** a pull request targeting a `release-*` branch\n29: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-build` with the same steps as for `main`\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: PR to feature branch does NOT trigger workflow\n33: - **GIVEN** a pull request targeting a `feature/*` branch\n34: - **WHEN** the PR is opened\n35: - **THEN** the `main.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Docker build failure fails the check\n38: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile contains a syntax error\n39: - **WHEN** `make docker-build` executes in the workflow\n40: - **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## Workflow 2: lint.yml ŌĆö Go Lint\n45: \n46: ### Requirement: Path-filtered Go lint on PR\n47: \n48: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/lint.yml` that runs `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Go file changes trigger lint\n51: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter `lint` matches `**/*.go`\n52: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: go.mod changes trigger lint\n56: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `go.mod` or `go.sum`\n57: - **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: .golangci.yml changes trigger lint\n61: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `.golangci.yml`\n62: - **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL match (`.golangci.yml` is in the filter paths) and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Workflow file changes trigger lint\n66: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n67: - **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Lint workflow SHALL run\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: No Go changes skip lint\n71: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `docs/README.md`\n72: - **WHEN** the path filter `lint` is evaluated\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the Lint workflow SHALL skip the lint job\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Lint failure fails the check\n76: - **GIVEN** Go source code contains a golangci-lint violation\n77: - **WHEN** `make lint` executes\n78: - **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## Workflow 3: test-coverage.yml ŌĆö Test Coverage\n83: \n84: ### Requirement: Race-enabled coverage tests on PR/merge_group\n85: \n86: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` that runs race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, with optional Codecov upload.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Coverage test on PR\n89: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` and path filter `coverage` matches\n90: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Coverage test on merge_group\n94: - **GIVEN** a `merge_group` event and path filter `coverage` matches\n95: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs\n96: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the same coverage command as for PR\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Coverage artifact upload\n99: - **GIVEN** the coverage test completes successfully\n100: - **WHEN** the post-test step runs\n101: - **THEN** `coverage.out` SHALL be uploaded as a workflow artifact\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Optional Codecov upload\n104: - **GIVEN** the `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret is configured and passed via `workflow_call`\n105: - **WHEN** the coverage job completes\n106: - **THEN** it SHALL upload the coverage report to Codecov via `codecov/codecov-action`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Codecov upload skipped when token absent\n109: - **GIVEN** the `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret is not configured\n110: - **WHEN** the coverage job completes\n111: - **THEN** the Codecov upload step SHALL be skipped without failing the workflow\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Coverage path filter excludes docs/media\n114: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.md`, `*.svg`, or `*.png` files\n115: - **WHEN** the path filter `coverage` is evaluated\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the coverage job SHALL be skipped\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Free disk space step\n119: - **GIVEN** the runner has limited disk space\n120: - **WHEN** the coverage job starts\n121: - **THEN** it SHALL run a `free-disk-space` step to ensure sufficient space for coverage data\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## Workflow 4: e2e.yml ŌĆö E2E Tests\n126: \n127: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind cluster\n128: \n129: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` that runs `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: E2E job on PR to main\n132: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n133: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n134: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Kind installation\n137: - **GIVEN** the E2E workflow is running\n138: - **WHEN** the Kind setup step executes\n139: - **THEN** it SHALL install Kind tool `v0.30.0` with `install_only: true`\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: E2E test execution\n142: - **GIVEN** the Kind cluster is ready\n143: - **WHEN** the E2E step runs\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make e2e` with Go `1.23`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: E2E failure uploads logs\n147: - **GIVEN** `make e2e` fails\n148: - **WHEN** the workflow reaches the post-test step\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL upload the `e2e-logs` directory as a workflow artifact\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: E2E cleanup always runs\n152: - **GIVEN** the E2E workflow completes (pass or fail)\n153: - **WHEN** the cleanup step executes\n154: - **THEN** it SHALL always run `make e2e-clean`\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: E2E uses ubuntu runner\n157: - **GIVEN** the E2E workflow is triggered\n158: - **WHEN** the job runner is selected\n159: - **THEN** it SHALL use an Ubuntu runner with Kind capability\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Workflow 5: codegen-check.yml ŌĆö Codegen Check\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: Code generation drift detection\n166: \n167: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` that verifies generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: API changes trigger codegen check\n170: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `pkg/apis/**`\n171: - **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Hack directory changes trigger codegen check\n175: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `hack/**`\n176: - **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n177: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Workflow changes trigger codegen check\n180: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `.github/workflows/**`\n181: - **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: Makefile changes trigger codegen check\n185: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies the `Makefile`\n186: - **WHEN** the path filter `codegen` is evaluated\n187: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Codegen Check workflow SHALL run\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Codegen check uses Go 1.24.4\n190: - **GIVEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs\n191: - **WHEN** Go is set up\n192: - **THEN** it SHALL use version `1.24.4`\n193: \n194: #### Scenario: Gen-check runs gen-all and diff\n195: - **GIVEN** the codegen check job is executing\n196: - **WHEN** the check step runs\n197: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` followed by `git diff --exit-code`)\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Generated code drift fails the check\n200: - **GIVEN** generated files are out of sync with source (e.g., CRD changed but not regenerated)\n201: - **WHEN** `make gen-check` executes\n202: - **THEN** `git diff --exit-code` SHALL detect the difference and the workflow SHALL fail\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## Workflow 6: copyright-check.yml ŌĆö Copyright Check\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Copyright header verification\n209: \n210: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` that ensures `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Source file changes trigger copyright check\n213: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies a Go source file\n214: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n215: - **THEN** it SHALL match (Go files are not in the exclusion list) and the Copyright Check workflow SHALL run\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Markdown changes skip copyright check\n218: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.md` files\n219: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n220: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match (`*.md` is excluded) and the workflow SHALL skip\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: SVG/PNG changes skip copyright check\n223: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies `*.svg` or `*.png` files\n224: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n225: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Docs directory changes skip copyright check\n228: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies files under `docs/**`\n229: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n230: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: .github directory changes skip copyright check\n233: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies files under `.github/**`\n234: - **WHEN** the path filter `copyright` is evaluated\n235: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the workflow SHALL skip\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Copyright check installs moreutils\n238: - **GIVEN** the copyright check job is running\n239: - **WHEN** the setup step executes\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (providing `sponge`) via `apt-get`\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Copyright gen produces no diff\n243: - **GIVEN** all source files have correct copyright headers\n244: - **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` runs followed by `git diff --exit-code`\n245: - **THEN** the diff SHALL be empty and the workflow SHALL pass\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Missing copyright header fails the check\n248: - **GIVEN** a new source file lacks the required copyright header\n249: - **WHEN** `make gen-copyright` runs followed by `git diff --exit-code`\n250: - **THEN** the diff SHALL detect the added header and the workflow SHALL fail\n251: \n252: ---\n253: \n254: ## Workflow 7: codespell.yml ŌĆö Codespell\n255: \n256: ### Requirement: Spelling check on PR\n257: \n258: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` that runs codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: Codespell runs on PR to main\n261: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n262: - **WHEN** the Codespell workflow runs\n263: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository and install codespell via `pip install codespell`\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: False-positive files are temporarily moved\n266: - **GIVEN** the codespell job is about to run\n267: - **WHEN** the pre-check step executes\n268: - **THEN** it SHALL back up and remove `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` from the repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation with skip patterns\n271: - **GIVEN** false-positive files have been moved\n272: - **WHEN** codespell runs\n273: - **THEN** it SHALL use `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on the `.` directory\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Files are restored after codespell\n276: - **GIVEN** codespell has completed (pass or fail)\n277: - **WHEN** the post-check step executes\n278: - **THEN** it SHALL restore all backed-up files to their original locations\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Spelling error fails the check\n281: - **GIVEN** a source file contains a misspelled word not in the ignore list\n282: - **WHEN** codespell runs\n283: - **THEN** it SHALL report the error and the workflow SHALL fail\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## Workflow 8: python-sdk-tests.yml ŌĆö Python SDK Tests\n288: \n289: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests on path change\n290: \n291: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` that runs pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: SDK file changes trigger tests\n294: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `sdk-python/**`\n295: - **WHEN** the path filter `sdk` is evaluated\n296: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python SDK Tests workflow SHALL run\n297: \n298: #### Scenario: Python 3.12 is used\n299: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests job is running\n300: - **WHEN** Python is set up\n301: - **THEN** it SHALL use version `3.12`\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: Editable install\n304: - **GIVEN** the Python SDK Tests job is in the `sdk-python/` working directory\n305: - **WHEN** the setup step executes\n306: - **THEN** it SHALL run `pip install -e .`\n307: \n308: #### Scenario: Pytest execution\n309: - **GIVEN** the SDK is installed in editable mode\n310: - **WHEN** the test step runs\n311: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n312: \n313: #### Scenario: SDK test failure fails the check\n314: - **GIVEN** a Python SDK test is failing\n315: - **WHEN** `python -m pytest tests/ -v` executes\n316: - **THEN** the workflow job SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n317: \n318: #### Scenario: No SDK changes skip tests\n319: - **GIVEN** a pull request only modifies Go source files\n320: - **WHEN** the path filter `sdk` is evaluated\n321: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT match and the Python SDK Tests workflow SHALL skip\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## Workflow 9: python-lint.yml ŌĆö Python Lint\n326: \n327: ### Requirement: Python lint with Ruff\n328: \n329: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` that runs Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: CLI code changes trigger Python lint\n332: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `cmd/cli/**`\n333: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n334: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: SDK changes trigger Python lint\n337: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `sdk-python/**`\n338: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n339: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Example code changes trigger Python lint\n342: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files under `example/**`\n343: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n344: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Test Python files trigger lint\n347: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies files matching `test/**/*.py`\n348: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: pyproject.toml changes trigger lint\n352: - **GIVEN** a pull request modifies `pyproject.toml`\n353: - **WHEN** the path filter `python` is evaluated\n354: - **THEN** it SHALL match and the Python Lint workflow SHALL run\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Python lint uses Python 3.10\n357: - **GIVEN** the Python Lint job is running\n358: - **WHEN** Python is set up\n359: - **THEN** it SHALL use version `3.10`\n360: \n361: #### Scenario: Ruff check execution\n362: - **GIVEN** Python is set up and ruff is installed\n363: - **WHEN** the lint step runs\n364: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: Ruff violation fails the check\n367: - **GIVEN** a Python file contains a Ruff-detectable issue\n368: - **WHEN** `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` executes\n369: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL fail with a non-zero exit code\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ## Workflow 10: build-push-release.yml ŌĆö Build and Push Release Images\n374: \n375: ### Requirement: Multi-architecture release image publication\n376: \n377: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` that builds and pushes multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Push to main builds latest images\n380: - **GIVEN** a push event to the `main` branch\n381: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n382: - **THEN** `TAG` SHALL be set to `latest` and multi-arch images SHALL be built and pushed\n383: \n384: #### Scenario: Semantic version tag builds tagged images\n385: - **GIVEN** a push event with `github.ref_type` equal to `tag` matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*`\n386: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n387: - **THEN** `TAG` SHALL be set to `github.ref_name` (e.g., `v0.1.0`) and images SHALL be tagged accordingly\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: GHCR login\n390: - **GIVEN** the release build job is running\n391: - **WHEN** the registry login step executes\n392: - **THEN** it SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Image registry is set correctly\n395: - **GIVEN** the release build job is running\n396: - **WHEN** the build steps execute\n397: - **THEN** `IMAGE_REGISTRY` SHALL be set to `ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Workloadmanager image is built and pushed\n400: - **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n401: - **WHEN** the workloadmanager build step executes\n402: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-workloadmanager` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE`\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: Router image is built and pushed\n405: - **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n406: - **WHEN** the router build step executes\n407: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-router` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `ROUTER_IMAGE`\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: Picod image is built and pushed\n410: - **GIVEN** the release workflow is running\n411: - **WHEN** the picod build step executes\n412: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-picod` with the correct `IMAGE_REGISTRY` and `PICOD_IMAGE`\n413: \n414: #### Scenario: Non-matching tag does NOT trigger release\n415: - **GIVEN** a push event with a tag that does NOT match semantic versioning (e.g., `docs-update`)\n416: - **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n417: - **THEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n418: \n419: #### Scenario: Feature branch push does NOT trigger release\n420: - **GIVEN** a push to a `feature/*` branch\n421: - **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n422: - **THEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n423: \n424: ---\n425: \n426: ## Workflow 11: dify-plugin-publish.yml ŌĆö Dify Plugin Publish\n427: \n428: ### Requirement: Dify plugin packaging and PR submission\n429: \n430: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` that packages a Dify plugin and automatically submits a PR to the `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository when a `dify-plugin/v*` tag is pushed.\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers publish\n433: - **GIVEN** a push event with tag matching `dify-plugin/v*`\n434: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n435: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository and package the Dify plugin\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: Plugin packaging\n438: - **GIVEN** the dify-plugin-publish workflow is running\n439: - **WHEN** the packaging step executes\n440: - **THEN** it SHALL create a distributable plugin archive from the `dify-plugin/` directory\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: PR submission to langgenius/dify-plugins\n443: - **GIVEN** the plugin is packaged\n444: - **WHEN** the PR submission step executes\n445: - **THEN** it SHALL use `peter-evans/create-pull-request` to create a PR against `langgenius/dify-plugins`\n446: \n447: #### Scenario: PLUGIN_ACTION secret is used for authentication\n448: - **GIVEN** the PR submission step requires cross-repo access\n449: - **WHEN** the step executes\n450: - **THEN** it SHALL use the `PLUGIN_ACTION` secret for authentication\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: Non-dify-plugin tag does NOT trigger workflow\n453: - **GIVEN** a push event with tag `v0.1.0` (not matching `dify-plugin/v*`)\n454: - **WHEN** the workflow trigger is evaluated\n455: - **THEN** the `dify-plugin-publish.yml` workflow SHALL NOT be triggered\n456: \n457: ---\n458: \n459: ## Workflow 12: workflows-approve.yml ŌĆö Approve Workflows\n460: \n461: ### Requirement: Automated workflow approval for repeat contributors\n462: \n463: The system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` that optionally approves pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n464: \n465: #### Scenario: pull_request_target on labeled event\n466: - **GIVEN** a `pull_request_target` event on `main` or `release-*` with `labeled` or `synchronize` type\n467: - **WHEN** the workflow is triggered\n468: - **THEN** it SHALL evaluate the contributor's PR history\n469: \n470: #### Scenario: Repeat contributor is auto-approved\n471: - **GIVEN** the PR author has more than one PR in the repository\n472: - **WHEN** the approval step executes\n473: - **THEN** it SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: ok-to-test label triggers approval\n476: - **GIVEN** the PR has the `ok-to-test` label (regardless of contributor history)\n477: - **WHEN** the approval step executes\n478: - **THEN** it SHALL approve all pending workflow runs for the PR\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: First-time contributor without label is NOT approved\n481: - **GIVEN** the PR author has only one PR and the PR does NOT have the `ok-to-test` label\n482: - **WHEN** the approval step evaluates\n483: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT approve any workflow runs\n484: \n485: #### Scenario: No action_required runs to approve\n486: - **GIVEN** all workflow runs for the head SHA have already started or completed\n487: - **WHEN** the approval step lists runs with `status: action_required`\n488: - **THEN** the list SHALL be empty and the step SHALL succeed without action\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ## Workflow Trigger Matrix\n493: \n494: ### Requirement: Workflow trigger correctness\n495: \n496: Each workflow SHALL be triggered only by the events specified in the trigger matrix.\n497: \n498: #### Scenario: PR to main triggers 9 workflows\n499: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` with changes across all paths\n500: - **WHEN** the PR is opened\n501: - **THEN** the following workflows SHALL be triggered: `main.yml`, `lint.yml`, `test-coverage.yml`, `e2e.yml`, `codegen-check.yml`, `copyright-check.yml`, `codespell.yml`, `python-sdk-tests.yml`, `python-lint.yml`\n502: \n503: #### Scenario: Push to main triggers release workflow\n504: - **GIVEN** a push to `main`\n505: - **WHEN** the push event is processed\n506: - **THEN** only `build-push-release.yml` SHALL be triggered (with `TAG=latest`)\n507: \n508: #### Scenario: Semantic version tag triggers release workflow\n509: - **GIVEN** a push of tag `v0.2.0`\n510: - **WHEN** the push event is processed\n511: - **THEN** only `build-push-release.yml` SHALL be triggered (with `TAG=v0.2.0`)\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: Dify plugin tag triggers plugin publish\n514: - **GIVEN** a push of tag `dify-plugin/v1.0.0`\n515: - **WHEN** the push event is processed\n516: - **THEN** only `dify-plugin-publish.yml` SHALL be triggered\n517: \n518: #### Scenario: PR labeled ok-to-test triggers approval\n519: - **GIVEN** a PR to `main` receives the `ok-to-test` label\n520: - **WHEN** the `labeled` event fires\n521: - **THEN** `workflows-approve.yml` SHALL be triggered\n522: \n523: ---\n524: \n525: ## Path Filter Configuration\n526: \n527: ### Requirement: dorny/paths-filter usage\n528: \n529: All workflows that use conditional path-based execution SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` with correctly configured path patterns.\n530: \n531: #### Scenario: lint filter matches Go files\n532: - **GIVEN** the `lint.yml` workflow defines filter `lint`\n533: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n534: - **THEN** they SHALL include `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n535: \n536: #### Scenario: coverage filter excludes docs/media\n537: - **GIVEN** the `test-coverage.yml` workflow defines filter `coverage`\n538: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n539: - **THEN** they SHALL match `**` with negative patterns excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n540: \n541: #### Scenario: codegen filter matches generation inputs\n542: - **GIVEN** the `codegen-check.yml` workflow defines filter `codegen`\n543: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n544: - **THEN** they SHALL include `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n545: \n546: #### Scenario: copyright filter excludes non-code files\n547: - **GIVEN** the `copyright-check.yml` workflow defines filter `copyright`\n548: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n549: - **THEN** they SHALL match all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n550: \n551: #### Scenario: sdk filter matches Python SDK\n552: - **GIVEN** the `python-sdk-tests.yml` workflow defines filter `sdk`\n553: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n554: - **THEN** they SHALL include `sdk-python/**`\n555: \n556: #### Scenario: python filter matches all Python paths\n557: - **GIVEN** the `python-lint.yml` workflow defines filter `python`\n558: - **WHEN** the filter paths are inspected\n559: - **THEN** they SHALL include `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`\n560: \n561: ---\n562: \n563: ## Security\n564: \n565: ### Requirement: Secret management and permission minimization\n566: \n567: Workflows SHALL use secrets and permissions following the principle of least privilege.\n568: \n569: #### Scenario: GITHUB_TOKEN used only for registry login\n570: - **GIVEN** the `build-push-release.yml` workflow runs\n571: - **WHEN** the GHCR login step executes\n572: - **THEN** it SHALL use `GITHUB_TOKEN` with only the permissions required for container registry write access\n573: \n574: #### Scenario: CODECOV_TOKEN is optional\n575: - **GIVEN** the `test-coverage.yml` workflow runs\n576: - **WHEN** the Codecov upload step is evaluated\n577: - **THEN** it SHALL check for the presence of `CODECOV_TOKEN` and skip gracefully if absent\n578: \n579: #### Scenario: PLUGIN_ACTION secret for cross-repo access\n580: - **GIVEN** the `dify-plugin-publish.yml` workflow runs\n581: - **WHEN** the PR creation step executes\n582: - **THEN** it SHALL use `PLUGIN_ACTION` secret for authentication to the external `langgenius/dify-plugins` repository\n583: \n584: #### Scenario: pull_request_target is NOT used for code execution\n585: - **GIVEN** the `workflows-approve.yml` workflow\n586: - **WHEN** the workflow is inspected\n587: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pull_request_target` ONLY for the approval action (which does not execute repository code), not for any step that checks out or runs repository code\n588: \n589: ---\n590: \n591: ## File Changes\n592: \n593: | Action | File | Description |\n594: |--------|------|-------------|\n595: | Create | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow: Docker build on PR to main/release-* |\n596: | Create | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go Lint: path-filtered golangci-lint on Go file changes |\n597: | Create | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage: race-enabled coverage tests with optional Codecov upload |\n598: | Create | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | E2E Tests: Kind-based E2E testing with log artifact upload on failure |\n599: | Create | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check: detect drift between generated artifacts and source |\n600: | Create | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check: verify copyright headers via make gen-copyright |\n601: | Create | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Codespell: spelling check with false-positive file handling |\n602: | Create | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests: pytest on sdk-python changes |\n603: | Create | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python Lint: Ruff check on Python path changes |\n604: | Create | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release: multi-arch images to GHCR on main push or version tag |\n605: | Create | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish: package plugin and PR to langgenius/dify-plugins |\n606: | Create | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows: auto-approve pending runs for repeat contributors |\n\n(End of file - total 606 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) ŌĆö Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `.github`\n- **Language:** YAML\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** (No directly matching specs)\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the creation of 12 GitHub Actions workflow files under `.github/workflows/` that provide a complete CI/CD pipeline for the AgentCube project. The workflows SHALL cover PR build verification, Go linting, test coverage, E2E testing on Kind, code generation drift checks, copyright/spelling checks, Python SDK tests and linting, multi-architecture release image publication, Dify plugin publishing, and automated workflow approval for repeat contributors. All workflows SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for path-based conditional execution where applicable, and SHALL consume Makefile targets defined in AR-033 without modifying any existing source code, Dockerfiles, or Helm charts.\n\n---\n\n## Workflow 1: main.yml ŌĆö Agentcube CI Workflow\n\n### Requirement: Docker build on PR to main/release-*\n\nThe system SHALL provide `.github/workflows/main.yml` that builds the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879189245,"end":1775879189263}}}}
